DENGUE - COLOMBIA (02)
**********************
Date: Tue, 22 Jul 1997 21:19:10 -0700
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
[see
Dengue - Colombia: under-/mis-reporting 970329161801
Dengue - Colombia archive number not yet assigned]
The following background information on dengue in Colombia was extracted
from GIDEON software:
Potential for transmission exists along the Atlantic coast, Magdalena River
Valley, Cauca River Valley, Putumayo Intendancy and Cordillera Oriental
slopes.
No cases were reported during 1960 to 1970. 9,894 cases were reported in
1980. 10,790 cases were reported in 1981; 6,776 in 1982; 12,919 in 1983;
7,540 in 1984;
Dengue hemorrhagic fever (DHF) was first reported in 1985. 82,272 were
reported in 1985 (including 1 DHF, fatal); 7,881 in 1986; 17,510 in 1987;
16,308 in 1988; 10,092 in 1989 (1 DHF); 17,389 (including 39 of DHF & one
fatality) in 1990.
15,103 cases (including 97 of DHF) were reported in 1991; 59,357 (496 DHF, 4
fatal) in 1992; 8,449 in 1993; 774 in 1994; 18,398 (107 DHF, 10 fatal) in
1995; 7,787 (12 fatal) in 1996.
---
Stephen A. Berger, M.D.
Tel Aviv Medical Center
e-mail: <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>
